      'In the same town lived Malik Bhago, a rich and corrupt government official. He hosted a grand feast for holy men to earn religious merit. When he learned that Guru Nanak was in town but had chosen a low-caste carpenter over his feast, his ego was bruised.',
      'Malik Bhago summoned Guru Nanak and demanded to know why his rich food was rejected in favor of Bhai Lalo\'s dry bread. Guru Ji calmly asked for a piece of bread from Malik Bhago\'s feast and a piece of coarse bread from Bhai Lalo\'s home.',
