      "The turtle eagerly promised to keep his mouth firmly shut. The geese took off, carrying the turtle high over the villages and fields.",
      "As they flew over a town, some children looked up in amazement and shouted, 'Look! Two clever birds are carrying a stupid turtle on a stick! What a funny sight!'",
      "The turtle, who was very proud and quick-tempered, was furious at being called stupid. Forgetting his promise and the fact that he was thousands of feet in the air, he opened his mouth to shout back, 'If my friends want to carry me, what is it to you, you foolish children!'",
      "The moment he opened his mouth, he lost his grip on the stick. He plummeted to the ground and was shattered on the rocks below. The geese could only fly on with deep sorrow for their foolish friend."
